Author: LowCalPal
Text: I used to have this happen too when I was at my lowest point.  It's like your body just forgets how to send food all the way through.

Author: cocoakobra
Text: Oh my god finally someone else makes a post about this phenomenon. I feel like my body is so used to just ejecting everything that it does it even when I wasn’t planning on purging.  And that makes the temptation to purge when I *do* want to so much harder to fight. My brain is like “well, it wants to come up anyway, who am I to deny it?”
